<br>
Why are clerics so damn bad at math?  It seems to be very prevalent in Sebilis.  Somehow, the use of a stack of peridots (exactly 210p) equates to the necessity for the cleric to keep ALL the gems that drop which often add up to 2kp or more.  Now, I went to school in a very small town and maybe our math was different, but I was taught that 210 does NOT equal 2000.<br>
<br>
Is it that they feel they deserve all 2k because of that raid they went on the day before that didn't reimburse them?  Is this my problem? Should I get screwed out of my share of loot so they can fund raids I wasn't on?<br>
<br>
My favorite:<br>
<br>
I joined a group forming up.  Cleric only had 2 peridots left. I usually carry 8 or so stacks of them on me (I supply them for clerics on raids I lead), so I handed the cleric a stack.  We kill frogs for a few hours. Time for the group to break up and the cleric splits the cash and then starts casting gate.  I immediately tell him to stop and he aborts the gate.  A conversation in group chat ensues:<br>
Me: &quot;What about the 10 or so money items we got? Shouldn't we divvy those up?&quot; (Note that I'm not even expecting to skim to cover the dots I gave).<br>
Cleric: &quot;It's traditional for the cleric to keep them to cover the cost of his peridots used for symbol.&quot;  <br>
Me: &quot;How many dots you have left?&quot;<br>
Cleric: &quot;6&quot;<br>
Me: &quot;How many dots did you come here with? Now think about it hard because we all already know the answer.&quot;<br>
Cleric: &quot;Umm... 2&quot;<br>
Me: &quot;Then what the fvck makes you think you have the right to keep the money items when you didn't even use your own @#%$ peridots. I suggest you divvy up the loot now before the 5 of us petition you, sir.&quot;<br>
Cleric: &quot;But the reason I only had 2 is because yesterday's group didn't get any cash items so I couldn't buy more.&quot;<br>
Me: &quot;And this is our problem how?&quot;<br>
Cleric: &quot;You know, you sure are rude.  I'll share the items, but don't ever expect to be invited to my group again.&quot;<br>
Me: &quot;Fine. I already put you on my 'do not group with' list anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
We split up the items.  One of the other group members gives me her share to cover the dots I gave the cleric.  We all live happily ever after, but gd that burns me.  And it's not even that I'm so poor that I really care about the cash. It's the attitude.  Too many clerics seem to think they're doing me a service by grouping with me.  Well I have news for them. I don't *need* a cleric. I can solo... and a lot better than a cleric can.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
